result.adr_address: 38-40 Davis St, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 38-40 Davis St, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.name: 42nd Davis

reviews.text: Best happy hour in Kennedy Town. Craft beers at great prices and friendly staff. Very popular with the expat locals so expect a lively crowd. They also host a dubious prize winning contest for downing 10 pints of a local beer. Watch out for projectiles if this event is on. 10% service charge goes on all prices.

Solid pours of beer with a generous happy hour pricing. Food disappointed. Chicken was very salty. Natchos were Doritos chips with natchos cheese. Place gets stars because it's a bar so the beer benefits overshine the food.

Fantastic food and exceptional service. We've been coming here very frequently since it opened. A neighborhood gem, we love 42nd Davis as do their large crowd of regulars. Chef-owned, Roy and Emma are great, along with the rest of the staff. Roy's Italian training really comes through in the food. A range of great offers throughout the week.
Really love the food here.
Awesome service, great food and quality drinks.
